.TH "generic_pipe_buf_try_steal" 9 "generic_pipe_buf_try_steal" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
generic_pipe_buf_try_steal \- attempt to take ownership of a &pipe_buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" generic_pipe_buf_try_steal
.BI "(struct pipe_inode_info *pipe "  ","
.BI "struct pipe_buffer *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pipe" 12
the pipe that the buffer belongs to
.IP "buf" 12
the buffer to attempt to steal
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function attempts to steal the \fIstruct page\fP attached to
\fIbuf\fP. If successful, this function returns 0 and returns with
the page locked. The caller may then reuse the page for whatever
he wishes; the typical use is insertion into a different file
page cache.
